"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkmy_docusaurus=globalThis.webpackChunkmy_docusaurus||[]).push([[5179],{1966(n,e,t){t.r(e),t.d(e,{assets:()=>c,contentTitle:()=>r,default:()=>d,frontMatter:()=>o,metadata:()=>s,toc:()=>u});var s=t(5845),a=t(4848),i=t(8453);const o={},r=void 0,c={authorsImageUrls:[]},u=[];function l(n){const e={code:"code",pre:"pre",...(0,i.R)(),...n.components};return(0,a.jsx)(e.pre,{children:(0,a.jsx)(e.code,{className:"language-md",children:"---\ntitle: DevSecOps Explained for Beginners\ndescription: Learn DevSecOps from basics to lifecycle with real examples.\n---\n\n# \ud83d\udd10 DevSecOps Explained for Beginners\n\n> \ud83d\ude80 A simple guide to understanding DevSecOps and why it matters\n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udfa8 Slide Version (Canva)\n\n\ud83d\udc49 View full presentation here:  \n\ud83d\udd17 https://www.canva.com/design/DAG_uCMdKUU/sgVgyobe71QhR5-EtSNutg/edit?utm_content=DAG_uCMdKUU&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link2&utm_source=sharebutton\n\n---\n\n## \ud83e\udde9 What is DevSecOps?\n\nDevSecOps stands for:\n\n\ud83d\udc49 **Dev + Sec + Ops**\n\n- **Dev (Development):** Writing code  \n- **Sec (Security):** Protecting systems  \n- **Ops (Operations):** Running and maintaining infrastructure  \n\n\ud83d\udca1 The key idea:\n\n> All teams work **together, continuously, and automatically**\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udd04 DevSecOps Lifecycle\n\nA typical DevSecOps workflow includes:\n\n1. Collaboration & Communication  \n2. Threat Modeling  \n3. QA Integration  \n4. Security Checks & Scans  \n5. Vulnerability Management  \n6. CI/CD  \n7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)  \n8. Container Security  \n9. Key Management  \n10. Continuous Monitoring  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83e\udd1d 1. Collaboration & Communication\n\n### Why it matters\n\nTeams (Dev \u2013 Sec \u2013 Ops) should:\n\n- Work together  \n- Share information continuously  \n\n### Benefits\n\n- \ud83d\udd25 Early bug detection  \n- \ud83d\udd25 Fewer conflicts  \n- \ud83d\udd25 Faster development  \n- \ud83d\udd25 Stronger security  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83e\udde0 2. Threat Modeling\n\n### What is it?\n\nThinking like a hacker before building the system:\n\n> \u201cIf I were an attacker, where would I attack?\u201d\n\n### Key questions:\n\n- What does the system include?  \n- What are the critical assets?  \n- What threats exist?  \n- How can we prevent them?  \n\n\ud83d\udca1 Fixing issues early = cheaper and easier  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83e\uddea 3. QA Integration\n\n### Traditional approach \u274c\n\n1. Code  \n2. Deploy  \n3. Test at the end  \n\n\ud83d\udc49 Result:\n- Many bugs  \n- Delays  \n- Stress  \n\n---\n\n### DevSecOps approach \u2705\n\n- Test continuously  \n- Automate testing  \n\n\ud83d\udc49 Result:\n- Bugs found early  \n- Faster releases  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udd0d 4. Security Checks & Scans\n\n### SAST\n- Scan source code  \n- Find vulnerabilities before running  \n\n### DAST\n- Test running applications  \n- Simulate real-world attacks  \n\n\ud83c\udfaf Goal:\n> Detect vulnerabilities as early as possible  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f 5. Vulnerability Management\n\nSecurity is not just about finding bugs \u2014 it's about managing them.\n\n### Process:\n\n1. Scan  \n2. Assess severity  \n3. Prioritize  \n4. Fix continuously  \n\n\ud83d\udc49 Focus on critical issues first  \n\n---\n\n## \u2699\ufe0f 6. CI/CD\n\nCI/CD automates the development pipeline:\n\n- \u2705 Build automatically  \n- \u2705 Test automatically  \n- \u2705 Deploy automatically  \n- \u2705 Integrate security checks  \n\n\ud83d\udca1 Every code push triggers automation  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f 7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)\n\nInfrastructure is defined using code.\n\n### Benefits:\n\n- Easy to manage  \n- Consistent environments  \n- Reduced human error  \n\n---\n\n## \u26a1 Why DevSecOps?\n\n### Old way \u274c\n\n- Teams work separately  \n- Security comes late  \n\n\ud83d\udc49 Result:\n- Late bug detection  \n- Expensive fixes  \n\n---\n\n### DevSecOps way \u2705\n\n- Teams collaborate  \n- Security is built-in  \n\n\ud83d\udc49 Result:\n- Faster delivery  \n- Better security  \n- Higher efficiency  \n\n---\n\n## \ud83e\udde0 Final Thoughts\n\nDevSecOps is not just a process \u2014  \n\ud83d\udc49 it is a **mindset**\n\n> Build fast, but secure from the beginning.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udccc Summary\n\n- DevSecOps = Dev + Sec + Ops  \n- Focus on **automation + collaboration + security early**  \n- Essential skill for modern developers  \n\n---\n\n\ud83d\udd25 Start your DevSecOps journey today!\n"})})}function d(n={}){const{wrapper:e}={...(0,i.R)(),...n.components};return e?(0,a.jsx)(e,{...n,children:(0,a.jsx)(l,{...n})}):l(n)}},8453(n,e,t){t.d(e,{R:()=>o,x:()=>r});var s=t(6540);const a={},i=s.createContext(a);function o(n){const e=s.useContext(i);return s.useMemo(function(){return"function"==typeof n?n(e):{...e,...n}},[e,n])}function r(n){let e;return e=n.disableParentContext?"function"==typeof n.components?n.components(a):n.components||a:o(n.components),s.createElement(i.Provider,{value:e},n.children)}},5845(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"permalink":"/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps","editUrl":"https://github.com/tienthanh23072007-stack/my-doku/tree/main/blog/DevSecOps.md","source":"@site/blog/DevSecOps.md","title":"DevSecOps","description":"","date":"2026-03-30T14:37:11.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":2.01,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Guide to Creating a Blog with Docusaurus","permalink":"/my-doku/blog/huong-dan-dung-blog"}}')}}]);